s: May 13, 2024 - ADATA has been around for a long ... budget brand for several PC components. Its RAM is much the same, and what it lacks in bells and whistles it makes up for in affordability. The company offers regular RAM sticks that are great for standard desktops or servers, but the company also has an XPG line of gaming memory. XPG has the angular design for the heat spreader you would expect for a gaming product, and it's pretty affordable. You can get 16GB of memory from ADATA for $35 on Amazon...
